---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Cigna Global in Germany', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-german-system', text: 'vs German GKV/PKV', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'when-to-use', text: 'When Cigna Makes Sense', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Cigna', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Germany', href: '/countries/germany/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'germanyPrice', header: 'Germany (Age 40)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Inpatient + Day-patient', germanyPrice: '€160-210/mo' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Silver + Outpatient', germanyPrice: '€230-300/mo' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Gold + Enhanced', germanyPrice: '€320-420/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Germany"
  description="Guide to using Cigna Global in Germany. How it compares to GKV and PKV, visa compliance, and when international insurance makes sense."
  headline="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Germany"
  subheadline="Is Cigna Global the right choice for expats in Germany? Understand how it fits with Germany's mandatory insurance system."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/germany-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Cigna Global in Germany</h2>
  <p>
    Germany requires all residents to have health insurance—either public (GKV) or private (PKV). Cigna Global can serve as initial coverage for visa applications and as a transition solution, but most long-term residents eventually need to enroll in the German system.
  </p>
  <p>
    Cigna works well for the initial period, freelancers establishing themselves, and expats who may relocate from Germany.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Important: German Insurance Requirements</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Germany mandates enrollment in GKV or German PKV for long-term residents. International insurance like Cigna is typically a bridge solution. Consult with German authorities about long-term compliance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Germany Quote"
    description="See Cigna Global pricing for expats in Germany."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-german-system">vs German GKV/PKV</h2>

  <h3>Cigna vs Public Insurance (GKV)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GKV:</strong> Income-based premiums, family coverage included, stable costs</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Age-based premiums, individual policies, worldwide coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cigna vs Private German Insurance (PKV)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>German PKV:</strong> German-regulated, better long-term compliance, higher age costs</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Portable worldwide, English support, may not meet long-term requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="when-to-use">When Cigna Makes Sense in Germany</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Initial visa applications:</strong> Coverage while establishing residency</li>
    <li><strong>Job seeker visa:</strong> The 6-month period before employment</li>
    <li><strong>Freelancers (first year):</strong> While establishing and choosing German system</li>
    <li><strong>Those who may relocate:</strong> Portable coverage if you leave Germany</li>
    <li><strong>Supplementary coverage:</strong> Alongside GKV for enhanced benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Cigna in Germany</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>New arrivals (initial period)</li>
        <li>Job seekers before employment</li>
        <li>Freelancers establishing business</li>
        <li>Expats who may relocate</li>
        <li>Those wanting English support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Long-term residents (GKV or German PKV)</li>
        <li>Employees (GKV automatic enrollment)</li>
        <li>Those staying in Germany permanently</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Germany?"
    description="Get a personalized Cigna Global quote."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> German insurance requirements are complex. Verify compliance with German authorities and consider consulting an insurance advisor.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
